01:04.554 --> 01:06.153
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

01:06.155 --> 01:08.055
♪ Taking her clothes off,
gone take all mine ♪

01:08.057 --> 01:11.692
So sorry. I... tried texting.

01:11.694 --> 01:14.896
Oh, it's fine. He's paid
for all night, so come in.

01:14.898 --> 01:16.664
♪ Want you so bad I had
to break your mind ♪

01:16.666 --> 01:19.600
- Uh, Kat, this is...
- Trevor. How you doing?

01:19.602 --> 01:22.069
Yes, it's what you're thinking.
There are worse ways to mourn.

01:22.071 --> 01:23.838
I could be sitting at
home eating ice cream.

01:23.840 --> 01:27.108
It's General Phillips.
He says it's urgent.

01:27.110 --> 01:28.743
I've seen you somewhere.

01:28.745 --> 01:30.545
- It's a big city. I doubt it.
- In the paper,

01:30.547 --> 01:31.879
the cover of <i>The Wall Street Journal.</i>

01:31.881 --> 01:33.281
You read <i>The Wall Street Journal?</i>

01:33.283 --> 01:34.715
You were at funeral, looked really nice.

01:34.717 --> 01:36.083
Whose funeral was it?

01:36.085 --> 01:38.352
My husband's.

01:38.354 --> 01:40.221
I should be back in an hour.

01:42.257 --> 01:43.791
General Phillips.

01:43.793 --> 01:46.394
To what do I owe this pleasure?

01:46.396 --> 01:48.796
Operation North Star.

01:48.798 --> 01:50.464
I'm giving it the green light.

01:50.466 --> 01:52.233
Operation North Star?

01:52.235 --> 01:54.001
The humanitarian workers,
the plane crash...

01:54.003 --> 01:55.670
I worked this out with
Howard months ago.

01:55.672 --> 01:57.405
Oh, well, then, a plan
is already in place.

01:57.407 --> 01:58.472
Tell me about it.

01:58.474 --> 02:00.608
The care package has been delivered.

02:00.610 --> 02:03.477
Great. What's next?

02:03.479 --> 02:05.780
- You really don't know, do you?
- No, which is why...

02:05.782 --> 02:07.415
We should postpone.

02:07.417 --> 02:08.883
General, Howard's gone,

02:08.884 --> 02:10.751
and now I'm in charge of
the company he built.

02:10.752 --> 02:13.054
So whether I like it or not,

02:13.056 --> 02:15.556
I have to stand out, stand up.

02:15.558 --> 02:18.826
And I can't do that without
therapy, antidepressants,

02:18.828 --> 02:21.762
and people like you, who
Howard confided in...

02:21.764 --> 02:23.898
sometimes more than he confided in me.

02:23.900 --> 02:25.166
You're unprepared.

02:25.168 --> 02:27.168
So? Prepare me.

02:27.170 --> 02:29.971
The accident.

02:29.973 --> 02:33.240
The accident was no accident.

02:33.242 --> 02:34.642
SCOTTIE: What the world knows...

02:34.644 --> 02:37.078
an ISAP plane carrying relief workers

02:37.080 --> 02:39.981
went down last night in a remote
region of the Ural Mountains

02:39.983 --> 02:42.149
well inside the Russian border.

02:42.151 --> 02:45.653
What the world doesn't know...
It was downed on purpose by us.

02:45.655 --> 02:47.154
There were 17 fatalities.

02:47.156 --> 02:48.789
No, there were 17 dead people.

02:48.791 --> 02:51.292
- What's the difference?
- They were already dead...

02:51.294 --> 02:53.628
John Does from a morgue in Estonia.

02:53.630 --> 02:55.529
The crash took place near what we think

02:55.531 --> 02:57.498
is a secret Russian military base.

02:57.500 --> 02:58.933
The reason we think but don't know

02:58.935 --> 03:01.602
is that the Ruskies are using
some kind of ground-based signal

03:01.604 --> 03:03.504
to jam line-of-sight with our birds.

03:03.506 --> 03:05.940
Since we can't see by air,
we need boots on the ground.

03:05.942 --> 03:08.509
So you downed a plane.

03:08.511 --> 03:10.811
- Edgy.
- To avoid an international incident,

03:10.813 --> 03:13.848
Russia has invited a go-team
from NTSB to investigate

03:13.850 --> 03:16.317
in the hopes of ruling
out an act of terror.

03:16.319 --> 03:17.685
You and Tom are on that team.

03:17.687 --> 03:19.220
You need to get eyes on that facility.

03:19.222 --> 03:20.788
Any idea what we're gonna find?

03:20.790 --> 03:22.657
Intel indicates that
whatever's going on there

03:22.659 --> 03:25.359
is specifically targeting the U.S.

03:25.361 --> 03:27.061
That's it.

03:27.063 --> 03:31.632
♪

03:31.634 --> 03:34.702
Howard didn't tell me about this
operation with the Pentagon.

03:34.704 --> 03:37.338
I want to know if he was
hiding anything else.

03:37.340 --> 03:39.740
You're one of the few people who
knew that before Howard died,

03:39.742 --> 03:43.010
he went off his meds, that
he'd become paranoid.

03:43.012 --> 03:44.979
- I haven't told anyone.
- Which is why

03:44.981 --> 03:47.048
I need you to handle this personally.

03:47.050 --> 03:49.750
And confidentially. I
want an internal audit...

03:49.752 --> 03:52.253
every contract or financial transaction.

03:52.255 --> 03:54.755
Leave no stone unturned.

03:54.757 --> 03:57.591
♪

03:57.593 --> 03:59.160
RUSSIAN SOLDIER: I wasn't notified.

03:59.162 --> 04:00.861
You are going to have
to talk to my superior.

04:00.863 --> 04:02.430
TOM: Come on. Loo... You
have our credentials.

04:02.432 --> 04:03.998
I'm sorry. It's a restricted area.

04:04.000 --> 04:05.833
Guys, we were invited
here to do our job.

04:05.835 --> 04:07.568
Now, we can only do that on our own

04:07.570 --> 04:10.004
with complete access to
the entire debris field.

04:10.006 --> 04:11.405
And if that's gonna be a problem,

04:11.407 --> 04:13.507
we're gonna have to call the embassy.

04:15.777 --> 04:17.378
Take nothing. Touch nothing.

04:17.380 --> 04:19.914
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

04:19.916 --> 04:22.683
Thank you very much.

04:22.685 --> 04:24.452
Excuse me.

04:30.225 --> 04:31.792
On my signal.

04:42.904 --> 04:45.740
Fuel leak! Fuel leak!

04:45.742 --> 04:48.209
It's not secure! Everybody back!

04:48.211 --> 04:51.212
♪

04:53.381 --> 04:55.082
Okay, I'm on the move.

04:55.084 --> 04:57.084
- Where am I headed?
- Northeast, over the ridge.

04:57.086 --> 04:59.320
Half a klick to the clearing.

05:11.633 --> 05:14.401
You're moments away, Tom-Tom.
Now make a left.

05:23.478 --> 05:25.146
You get there, you snap some photos,

05:25.148 --> 05:28.182
and you get out before anyone
misses you at the crash site.

05:28.184 --> 05:29.750
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

05:29.752 --> 05:33.420
- You find it?
- I found something.

05:33.422 --> 05:36.457
(CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING)

05:36.459 --> 05:38.192
Sure as hell isn't a weapons facility.

05:38.194 --> 05:39.426
What is it? Come on.

05:39.428 --> 05:41.529
Don't leave the D-man out of this.

05:44.032 --> 05:45.633
I don't know.

05:45.635 --> 05:48.002
I think you're gonna have to
see this one to believe it.

05:48.004 --> 05:50.604
- Hey!
- _

05:50.606 --> 05:53.507
I don't... I-I don't
know what you're saying!

05:53.509 --> 05:54.592
(GUN COCKS)

05:54.616 --> 05:56.499
_

05:58.898 --> 06:00.280
_

06:00.282 --> 06:01.949
Hey, hey! Why didn't anybody tell us

06:01.951 --> 06:03.617
there was an active fuel leak, huh?

06:03.619 --> 06:07.121
Now I got to report this to
your superiors in Moscow.

06:09.591 --> 06:11.458
So, what's over the hill
and through the woods?

06:11.460 --> 06:13.661
Grandma's house, if she lived in Topeka.

06:13.663 --> 06:15.196
I guess we're not in
Kansas anymore, Toto.

06:15.198 --> 06:16.864
I wouldn't bet on it.

06:20.168 --> 06:21.235
What's this?

06:21.237 --> 06:23.037
A numbered account in the Dutch Antilles

06:23.039 --> 06:24.371
registered to an I.P. address

06:24.373 --> 06:26.707
matching Howard's
computer at your house.

06:28.710 --> 06:30.177
Did you find anything else?

06:30.179 --> 06:31.745
No, except for a troubling line item

06:31.747 --> 06:33.714
listed only as "Iran-Contra."

06:33.716 --> 06:36.183
- What was the account used for?
- I don't know.

06:36.185 --> 06:39.353
Briar Metcalf might. He's
the one who set it up.

06:39.355 --> 06:41.155
Briar. Of course.

06:41.157 --> 06:43.190
Would you like me to go see him?

06:43.192 --> 06:44.425
Desperately.

06:44.427 --> 06:47.328
But I need to do it.

06:47.330 --> 06:48.929
Where are we?

06:48.931 --> 06:52.233
Independence... population 216.

06:56.404 --> 06:58.706
What is it?

06:58.708 --> 07:00.241
During the Cold War, there were rumors

07:00.243 --> 07:02.710
that the Soviets built
replicas of American towns

07:02.712 --> 07:05.045
to train their agents
how to live like us.

07:05.047 --> 07:06.847
No one ever proved they existed.

07:06.849 --> 07:08.716
You know, a place to
train sleeper agents

07:08.718 --> 07:11.552
made sense back in the day. But
today, when you can get a visa

07:11.554 --> 07:13.387
and send them to Disneyland?

07:13.389 --> 07:15.189
What are they up to?

07:15.191 --> 07:17.057
Should we inform General Phillips?

07:17.059 --> 07:20.261
No. Not until we know
what we're dealing with.

07:20.263 --> 07:22.029
Seems like maybe you already do.

07:22.031 --> 07:24.798
I don't, but I know someone who might.

07:26.902 --> 07:29.436
MAN: Hey, hey. Men only!

07:29.438 --> 07:31.472
I'll let you know if I see any.

07:36.878 --> 07:39.713
I said I couldn't help you.

07:39.715 --> 07:42.483
Yes, but you didn't mean
it, not after Riga.

07:42.485 --> 07:45.119
Please, don't push me on this.

07:45.121 --> 07:46.921
You don't know the people involved.

07:46.923 --> 07:48.889
Acquaint me.

07:53.895 --> 07:56.664
They inserted agents
at Three Mile Island,

07:56.666 --> 08:01.335
at O'Hare Airport before Flight
191 went down in Chicago,

08:01.337 --> 08:03.704
agents that were trained
in towns like this

08:03.706 --> 08:06.407
to infiltrate America.

08:06.409 --> 08:08.242
Then the wall fell,

08:08.244 --> 08:10.878
and the program stopped.

08:10.880 --> 08:14.782
Mm. Doesn't looked
like it stopped to me.

08:14.784 --> 08:18.018
No. This new place

08:18.020 --> 08:20.020
is something else.

08:22.457 --> 08:25.092
Agents trained not just
to conceal themselves,

08:25.094 --> 08:27.428
but to...

08:27.430 --> 08:31.632
<i>slivat'sya...</i> to merge with
their cover identities.

08:31.634 --> 08:32.666
What does that mean?

08:32.668 --> 08:34.568
I hear only rumors

08:34.570 --> 08:38.839
that this program is the next
generation of what came before

08:38.841 --> 08:40.374
but even more dangerous.

08:40.376 --> 08:43.010
People are afraid to talk about it,

08:43.011 --> 08:45.846
people who aren't afraid of much.

08:45.848 --> 08:49.183
I need to get a look in there, Vadim.
It's important.

08:49.185 --> 08:52.186
Occasionally, some of
the new boys call me,

08:52.188 --> 08:54.555
ask for recommendations,

08:54.557 --> 08:56.623
agents or assets I may have had

08:56.625 --> 08:58.559
who are fluent in Russian or English.

08:58.561 --> 09:01.862
For assignment in Independence.

09:01.864 --> 09:04.698
You don't want to do this.

09:04.700 --> 09:07.067
I have two agents for you to recommend.

09:07.069 --> 09:09.069
Listen to what I'm telling you.

09:09.071 --> 09:13.007
I send agents in, but they
never come out... ever.

09:13.009 --> 09:16.076
I'll have two dossiers
for you within the hour.

09:22.217 --> 09:24.618
You think Scottie knows
more than she's saying?

09:24.620 --> 09:26.820
Every day of the week
and twice on Sunday.

09:26.822 --> 09:30.190
(CELLPHONE VIBRATES, CHIMES)

09:42.337 --> 09:44.905
I hope you're a quick study.

09:44.907 --> 09:46.573
- What's this?
- Your cover.

09:46.575 --> 09:49.843
You and Nez are FSB agents being
transferred to Independence.

09:49.845 --> 09:52.613
Nez? What about Solomon?

09:52.615 --> 09:53.914
I have another assignment for him.

09:53.916 --> 09:55.249
You're wheels-up in an hour.

09:55.251 --> 09:56.683
Two hours. I have an appointment.

09:56.685 --> 09:57.951
Cancel it.

09:57.953 --> 09:59.853
- I can't do that.
- Of course you can.

09:59.855 --> 10:02.589
Clearly you don't want to.

10:02.591 --> 10:04.024
Why?

10:04.026 --> 10:05.793
Who are you meeting with
that's so important?

10:05.795 --> 10:08.629
It's personal.

10:08.631 --> 10:10.831
Two hours, not a minute more.

10:21.709 --> 10:25.045
She's doing a complete audit.

10:25.047 --> 10:26.880
Tell me about Operation North Star.

10:26.882 --> 10:28.949
Accounts, case files, everything.

10:28.951 --> 10:30.918
The relief workers, the plane crash.

10:30.920 --> 10:33.287
- Has she taken the contract?
- She knows you hid things from her,

10:33.289 --> 10:35.589
and if she looks closely enough,
she's gonna find out it's me.

10:35.591 --> 10:37.925
Let me worry about her.
You worry about the op.

10:37.927 --> 10:39.259
Whoa.

10:39.261 --> 10:40.961
What is all this?

10:40.963 --> 10:43.063
It doesn't... It doesn't
matter, not now.

10:43.065 --> 10:45.432
Look, if I'm gonna work
with you, I need to know

10:45.434 --> 10:48.168
that you have a clear
head, that you're not...

10:48.170 --> 10:50.737
- that you're focused.
- I've never been more focused.

10:50.739 --> 10:53.307
Says the manic depressive
who's off his meds.

10:53.309 --> 10:55.642
She told you that?

10:55.644 --> 10:57.111
Clearly, you're not taking them.

10:57.113 --> 10:59.813
Which is why I can see the
truth, Tom, for the first time.

10:59.815 --> 11:01.348
What truth? Did you hear what I said?

11:01.350 --> 11:02.783
She's looking into what you're hiding.

11:02.785 --> 11:05.319
She is gonna find me out. You're
telling me that's not important,

11:05.321 --> 11:07.087
but some village in Siberia is?

11:07.089 --> 11:08.288
Yeah, it's critical.

11:08.290 --> 11:09.923
Critical to what?

11:09.925 --> 11:12.092
To everything. To the whole picture.

11:12.094 --> 11:13.660
That's what she doesn't want me to see.

11:13.662 --> 11:15.529
It's why she kept me medicated...

11:15.531 --> 11:18.799
to keep me from finding the truth.

11:18.801 --> 11:21.168
You have to get on that plane.

11:21.170 --> 11:23.904
You have to go to Russia
and see this through.

11:47.700 --> 11:50.567
_

11:59.349 --> 12:01.177
_

12:01.411 --> 12:04.653
_

12:10.070 --> 12:12.539
_

