12:54.367 --> 12:56.531
_

13:12.689 --> 13:15.825
From this moment on, you
will only speak English.

13:15.827 --> 13:17.460
No exceptions.

13:17.462 --> 13:18.928
This complex was built

13:18.930 --> 13:21.697
on the site of a former
missile facility.

13:21.699 --> 13:23.966
Ground water was polluted.

13:23.968 --> 13:25.368
Be aware of it.

13:25.370 --> 13:27.703
Short showers. Bottled water only.

13:27.705 --> 13:29.972
No exceptions.

13:29.974 --> 13:34.110
You will be given a new identity.

13:34.112 --> 13:36.112
Study it.

13:36.114 --> 13:37.613
Become it.

13:37.615 --> 13:39.215
It is you.

13:39.217 --> 13:43.552
Do not break character
for anything or anyone.

13:43.554 --> 13:46.489
You will be tested.

13:46.491 --> 13:48.824
You will be pushed.

13:48.826 --> 13:52.128
You will become someone new.

13:52.130 --> 13:54.196
You will receive your assignment

13:54.198 --> 13:58.567
and will take our fight to America.

14:02.672 --> 14:04.407
(SIGHS) I'm Lisa.

14:04.409 --> 14:06.509
I'm an unemployed bank teller.

14:06.511 --> 14:08.711
Oh, and I live with my brother. Hmm.

14:08.713 --> 14:10.012
Who's in construction.

14:10.014 --> 14:12.515
What fight could we
possibly bring to America?

14:12.517 --> 14:14.884
One no one will see coming.

14:14.886 --> 14:16.185
Who are you?

14:16.187 --> 14:18.154
Uh, I'm Stan.

14:18.156 --> 14:20.656
I'm a janitor, and...

14:20.658 --> 14:22.558
I live with my wife.

14:24.728 --> 14:26.829
TOM: Hello? Anyone home?

14:26.831 --> 14:29.498
CYNTHIA: In here, sweetie.

14:29.500 --> 14:31.400
I was wondering where you were.

14:31.402 --> 14:33.335
(CHUCKLES)

14:33.337 --> 14:34.870
(DOG BARKS QUIETLY)

14:34.872 --> 14:37.039
Hey. Hi, there.

14:37.041 --> 14:40.009
- Oh, Sam, leave Daddy alone.
- Oh, that's okay. Hi, boy.

14:40.011 --> 14:42.378
I'm just finishing up
the tuna casserole.

14:42.380 --> 14:44.880
I'll need about 15 minutes or so.

14:44.882 --> 14:48.284
You better change, or we'll be late.

14:48.286 --> 14:50.619
Uh, late... late for what?

14:50.621 --> 14:53.055
The Tugenbergs.

14:53.057 --> 14:54.857
Linda's birthday?

14:54.859 --> 14:56.091
- Right.
- (CHUCKLES)

14:56.093 --> 14:57.526
I swear you'd forget we were married

14:57.528 --> 14:59.361
if you didn't wake up
next to me every day.

14:59.363 --> 15:01.130
Yep. (CLEARS THROAT)

15:01.132 --> 15:02.598
Uh, smells great.

15:02.600 --> 15:04.567
Don't even think about it.

15:04.569 --> 15:06.302
Now shoo.

15:06.304 --> 15:08.304
Go on.

15:08.306 --> 15:10.773
Go put on the sweater I
got you for Christmas.

15:10.775 --> 15:12.641
Right. The, uh, sweater.

15:12.643 --> 15:14.944
- I laid it out on the bed.
- Of course you did.

15:14.946 --> 15:18.447
Along with your khakis
and your penny loafers.

15:18.449 --> 15:19.982
What would I do without you?

15:19.984 --> 15:23.619
Honestly, I shudder to think.

15:23.621 --> 15:26.188
(CHUCKLES)

15:26.190 --> 15:29.492
(CAR HORNS HONK, SIREN WAILS)

15:29.494 --> 15:32.828
(CELLPHONE RINGS)

15:32.830 --> 15:34.964
Hey, I am on my way home now.

15:34.966 --> 15:38.300
Open a bottle of Beaujolais
and let it breathe a while.

15:38.302 --> 15:41.337
Sorry, Briar. You're gonna
be late for that Beaujolais.

15:41.339 --> 15:43.072
- Scottie, what are you d...
- Briar, if I were you,

15:43.074 --> 15:45.641
I'd talk little and listen big.

15:45.643 --> 15:48.143
I don't want Mr. Solomon
to have to get bloodstains

15:48.145 --> 15:50.479
all over these aniline leather seats.

15:50.481 --> 15:51.780
The account in the Antilles,

15:51.782 --> 15:53.782
the one you set up for
Howard without telling me?

15:53.784 --> 15:55.351
I don't know what you're talking about.

15:55.353 --> 15:57.353
Howard was making secret
payments to someone.

15:57.355 --> 15:59.522
You would know who. I want a name.

16:02.192 --> 16:04.760
Effective immediately, you're
out as CFO of Halcyon.

16:04.762 --> 16:06.328
What you say next will determine

16:06.330 --> 16:08.264
if that's the worst thing
that happens to you today.

16:08.266 --> 16:09.932
Scottie, I would... Honestly.

16:09.934 --> 16:12.167
But Howard was like a brother to me.

16:12.169 --> 16:14.803
(LAUGHS) You know, funny thing.

16:14.805 --> 16:16.672
Most people think only
men can be brothers.

16:16.674 --> 16:18.040
I used to think that, too,

16:18.042 --> 16:19.875
until I stood face-to-face
with my executioner.

16:19.877 --> 16:23.512
Hand to God, I was a dead man.

16:23.514 --> 16:25.014
And that part where you're
supposed to see your life

16:25.016 --> 16:26.549
flash before your eyes, you
know what I saw instead?

16:26.551 --> 16:30.486
I saw the most (INHALES
SHARPLY) beautiful pair of legs

16:30.488 --> 16:32.454
staying the hand of my executioner.

16:32.456 --> 16:34.156
This woman,

16:34.158 --> 16:35.858
she's my brother.

16:35.860 --> 16:37.326
Owe her my life, really.

16:37.328 --> 16:41.230
And if she asks me to remove your head,

16:41.232 --> 16:43.799
I'll do so without thinking twice.

16:43.801 --> 16:47.970
So... let's get talking.

16:47.972 --> 16:50.205
Or... let's get surgical.

16:50.207 --> 16:52.007
Who did Howard give that money to?

16:52.009 --> 16:53.509
I-I-I don't know his name.

16:53.511 --> 16:55.010
Howard never told me.

16:55.012 --> 16:56.879
Then for the sake of your leather seats,

16:56.881 --> 17:00.416
I hope Howard told you
where we could find him.

17:00.418 --> 17:04.653
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

17:04.655 --> 17:06.321
You made it! (GASPS)

17:06.324 --> 17:08.357
Oh, my God. Please tell me
that's what I think it is.

17:08.358 --> 17:10.893
Nana's tuna casserole
straight from the oven.

17:10.895 --> 17:12.761
Happy birthday to me.

17:12.762 --> 17:15.064
Come on. Let me show
you where to put it.

17:17.901 --> 17:21.436
They offered me a full ride.
I-I could've gone pro.

17:21.439 --> 17:23.839
The coach said I had the arm for it.

17:23.840 --> 17:25.007
- Stanley.
- Hmm?

17:25.009 --> 17:26.407
You remember Angela and David.

17:26.410 --> 17:28.711
Uh, no, I don't think we've met.
Of course I remember them.

17:28.713 --> 17:30.546
She thinks I don't remember anything.

17:30.548 --> 17:33.048
- How was your trip?
- Oh, great.

17:33.050 --> 17:36.552
David's niece Joanne just
got married in Boca.

17:36.554 --> 17:40.356
Janelle. And it was Palm Beach.

17:40.358 --> 17:42.524
I think someone's had a
little too much punch.

17:42.526 --> 17:44.093
(ALL CHUCKLE)

17:46.429 --> 17:49.231
Well, I think weddings
are forgettable anyways.

17:49.233 --> 17:52.434
That's why we eloped
after only three days.

17:52.436 --> 17:56.805
Yep, it was four years ago in
a blizzard on February 2nd,

17:56.807 --> 18:00.509
the day of the hedge. Or the hog.

18:00.511 --> 18:01.810
- Or the, um...
- Uh, groundhog.

18:01.812 --> 18:04.113
- The... The groundhog.
- It was, uh, Groundhog Day.

18:04.115 --> 18:06.081
And, uh, the power was down,

18:06.083 --> 18:08.217
so I was bringing some ice
cream out to the fire escape

18:08.219 --> 18:11.420
'cause it was melting.
And, uh, there she was,

18:11.422 --> 18:13.288
doing the exact same thing.

18:13.290 --> 18:15.290
So we sat there and ate ice cream

18:15.292 --> 18:18.160
in the middle of a blizzard.

18:18.162 --> 18:21.130
Uh, there was this moment where you...

18:21.132 --> 18:23.499
turned and looked at me.

18:23.501 --> 18:25.167
And you were surrounded by snow,

18:25.169 --> 18:29.071
and you were caught in the
moonlight, and you smiled.

18:29.073 --> 18:32.241
I'll always remember it, because...

18:32.243 --> 18:34.910
it was the moment I
fell in love with you.

18:37.580 --> 18:40.215
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS CONTINUE)

18:43.920 --> 18:45.320
Based on the scale of downtown,

18:45.322 --> 18:47.790
we're looking at a community
that's at least a square mile.

18:47.792 --> 18:51.627
And Grushenka's watching
every inch of it.

18:51.629 --> 18:53.429
There has to be an op center.

18:53.431 --> 18:56.131
If we can find it, we can
figure out what's going on.

18:56.133 --> 18:58.133
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

18:58.135 --> 18:59.468
DAVID: How could you be so stupid?

18:59.470 --> 19:00.803
You've been warned about this before.

19:00.805 --> 19:02.471
ANGELA: I don't want to pretend anymore.

19:02.473 --> 19:04.873
- I just want to go home.
- Don't do this.

19:04.875 --> 19:06.709
Don't do what? Act normal?

19:06.711 --> 19:08.544
(SINGING STOPS)

19:10.680 --> 19:12.734
_

19:14.109 --> 19:15.500
_

19:16.094 --> 19:17.812
_

19:18.015 --> 19:19.375
_

19:20.086 --> 19:23.344
_

19:23.562 --> 19:25.555
_

19:26.531 --> 19:28.359
_

19:28.805 --> 19:30.414
_

19:40.577 --> 19:46.415
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

19:58.762 --> 20:01.663
- Hey.
- I thought you might want some company.

20:01.665 --> 20:03.031
What are you doing?

20:03.033 --> 20:06.268
Look, uh, Cynthia...

20:06.270 --> 20:09.338
Whatever your real name is,
they can't hear us in here.

20:09.340 --> 20:13.041
I know. I'm not doing it for them.

20:13.043 --> 20:15.444
No, stop.

20:15.446 --> 20:16.578
I'm married.

20:16.580 --> 20:18.781
We're not allowed to be married.

20:18.783 --> 20:20.415
I know. I lied.

20:20.417 --> 20:22.217
Sorry.

20:24.754 --> 20:27.289
You have a rash.

20:27.291 --> 20:30.425
Oh, everybody does. You do, too.

20:33.229 --> 20:35.030
What is this from?

20:35.032 --> 20:36.765
No one knows.

20:38.902 --> 20:41.937
If I leave now, they're gonna
see me and wonder why.

20:43.940 --> 20:46.141
So don't get out.

20:46.143 --> 20:47.943
I don't bite.

20:52.916 --> 20:56.485
What's your wife's name?

20:56.487 --> 20:59.421
Liz.

20:59.423 --> 21:02.758
Tell me about her, your other wife.

21:07.664 --> 21:10.999
Please. I'm better now.

21:12.802 --> 21:15.904
I'm afraid we both know that's not true.

21:18.328 --> 21:20.675
_

21:20.677 --> 21:22.477
No! No, no!

21:22.479 --> 21:23.912
Please!

21:23.914 --> 21:25.814
I can do better!

21:25.816 --> 21:28.584
I can do better! Please!

21:28.586 --> 21:31.286
Please! Aah!

21:50.069 --> 21:51.736
(EXHALES HEAVILY)

21:54.640 --> 21:57.275
Hey, Pete. You going somewhere?

21:59.678 --> 22:01.479
PETE: I've been transferred.

22:01.481 --> 22:03.314
To America.

22:03.316 --> 22:04.849
I leave in an hour.

22:04.851 --> 22:05.917
Transferred? That's great.

22:05.919 --> 22:08.486
Isn't that what... what we want?

22:11.924 --> 22:14.125
Don't you get it? I may not come back.

22:14.127 --> 22:16.694
Chances are I'll never come back.

22:21.812 --> 22:23.461
_

22:27.706 --> 22:30.809
Answer it.

22:30.811 --> 22:33.144
(CELLPHONE RINGS, BEEPS)

22:33.146 --> 22:34.512
Hello.

22:34.514 --> 22:37.916
Lisa, this is Mitchell
with First Street Bank.

22:37.918 --> 22:40.819
I'm calling to remind you
about our interview today.

22:40.821 --> 22:43.054
(TOM SIGHS)

22:43.056 --> 22:46.357
Sorry about last night.

22:46.359 --> 22:48.626
Can't really form attachments.

22:48.628 --> 22:50.695
Stan, what are you talking about?

22:50.697 --> 22:52.864
Sometimes you say the strangest things.

22:52.866 --> 22:54.699
Nobody knows when they're
sending us to America,

22:54.701 --> 22:56.835
unless you know something I don't.

22:57.406 --> 22:59.453
_

22:59.455 --> 23:02.265
_

23:05.678 --> 23:07.345
So, where should we go for breakfast?

23:07.347 --> 23:09.147
I'm famished.

23:09.149 --> 23:10.982
(TELEPHONES RINGING)

23:10.984 --> 23:13.751
Moved here recently, I see.

23:13.753 --> 23:15.753
From Ohio, yeah.

23:15.755 --> 23:18.223
What part of Ohio?

23:18.225 --> 23:19.991
Canton.

23:19.993 --> 23:23.094
Is that near Akron at all?

23:25.531 --> 23:29.200
It's about 40 minutes south.

23:29.202 --> 23:32.437
You know anyone here, made
any friends in town yet?

23:32.439 --> 23:33.771
I'm sorry, what does that have to...

23:33.773 --> 23:37.942
Please answer the question.

23:37.944 --> 23:40.945
No, I don't know anyone here.

23:43.515 --> 23:46.351
You know,

23:46.353 --> 23:50.088
I think you'd be a great
fit at First Street.

23:52.258 --> 23:56.427
But the applicant pool is pretty...

23:56.429 --> 23:59.898
stiff, I'm afraid.

23:59.900 --> 24:02.533
I would advise against that.

24:02.535 --> 24:04.636
It's about who you know.

24:04.638 --> 24:06.804
And since you need
help meeting people...

24:06.806 --> 24:08.273
Ohh!

24:08.275 --> 24:10.375
(CLATTER)

24:10.377 --> 24:11.943
(GRUNTING)

24:20.486 --> 24:23.655
(CLEARS THROAT)

24:23.657 --> 24:26.991
(SIGHS)

24:26.993 --> 24:29.227
Any more questions?

24:29.229 --> 24:30.495
(WHISTLE BLOWS)

24:30.497 --> 24:32.664
(CHEERS AND APPLAUSE)

24:41.173 --> 24:42.740
Just gonna grab a water.

24:46.612 --> 24:48.279
Found the command center.

24:48.281 --> 24:49.514
We should move tonight,

24:49.516 --> 24:50.982
uplink their system with Halcyon.

24:50.984 --> 24:52.350
Yeah, and get the hell out.

24:52.352 --> 24:54.352
My brother packed up
and left this morning.

24:54.354 --> 24:55.753
Transfer, he said.

24:55.755 --> 24:58.156
- So they're moving him already?
- Mm-hmm.

24:58.158 --> 25:00.325
- Any idea where they sent him?
- (CHUCKLES) No.

25:00.327 --> 25:02.860
But he was terrified. Don't drink that.

25:02.862 --> 25:04.929
- Why not?
- 'Cause I ran a 6-minute mile

25:04.931 --> 25:07.265
and beat the hell out of
a bank manager today.

25:07.267 --> 25:08.700
We're being doped.

25:08.702 --> 25:11.436
(SCOFFS) The rash.

25:11.438 --> 25:12.704
How?

25:12.706 --> 25:14.973
Something in the water. Low doses.

25:14.975 --> 25:17.041
Stimulant to enhance performance

25:17.043 --> 25:20.511
and lower inhibitions, relieve anxiety.

25:20.513 --> 25:21.813
They want us compliant

25:21.815 --> 25:23.514
so we don't ask questions
about this place.

25:23.516 --> 25:24.983
- How do you know all this?
- Lisa.

25:24.985 --> 25:27.719
- (WHISTLE BLOWS, CROWD CHEERS)
- Will you come with me?

25:27.721 --> 25:29.454
If this is about the bank, I...

25:29.456 --> 25:31.356
Please, just come with me.

25:35.561 --> 25:37.028
(WHISTLE BLOWS)

25:40.499 --> 25:42.800
GRUSHENKA: Do you know what this is?

25:42.802 --> 25:44.202
No.

25:46.205 --> 25:48.706
During the Second World War,

25:48.708 --> 25:52.043
the Red Army carried these
instead of standard tags.

25:52.045 --> 25:54.012
It's an identity capsule.

25:54.014 --> 25:59.150
A soldier's vitals are written
on a slip of paper inside.

25:59.152 --> 26:02.420
My grandfather's are in this one.

26:02.422 --> 26:06.858
Hasn't been opened since it was
used to identify his body,

26:06.860 --> 26:09.427
a life he gave for Russia.

26:11.430 --> 26:12.830
(CLICK)

26:16.001 --> 26:17.769
(<I>CLATTER</I>)

26:17.771 --> 26:22.440
You know, most candidates react
timid to that test, but not you.

26:22.442 --> 26:25.710
You have an instinct
that cannot be taught,

26:25.712 --> 26:27.211
a capability.

26:27.213 --> 26:28.746
I'm impressed.

26:28.748 --> 26:33.851
You are needed for the next
phase of our program here.

26:33.853 --> 26:36.054
(CLICK)

26:36.056 --> 26:38.222
Wait, my new identity?

26:38.224 --> 26:40.258
Lisa is a real person?

26:40.260 --> 26:44.195
This is Dr. Pirogov.

26:44.197 --> 26:48.032
I'll be performing your reassignment.

26:48.034 --> 26:50.234
GRUSHENKA: She's a very close match, no?

26:50.236 --> 26:51.869
She is.

26:51.871 --> 26:53.805
Based on the target's medical files,

26:53.807 --> 26:57.141
we'll need a slight alteration
of the mandible here

26:57.143 --> 26:59.811
and here,

26:59.813 --> 27:03.948
and a rhinoplasty to curve the nose.

27:03.950 --> 27:07.251
Even I won't be able to tell the
difference when we're through.

27:07.253 --> 27:09.554
♪

27:09.556 --> 27:11.889
Are you ready

27:11.891 --> 27:13.891
to give a life for Russia

27:13.893 --> 27:16.360
and to take on another?

27:26.863 --> 27:29.097
(CAR HORNS HONKING)

27:31.134 --> 27:34.463
- (KEYS JINGLE)
- (CHUCKLING) Whoa-ho-ho.

27:34.526 --> 27:37.393
Oh, you do not look like a man
who should get behind the wheel.

27:37.395 --> 27:40.430
Oh, yeah? Who the hell are you?

27:40.432 --> 27:42.165
Today?

27:42.167 --> 27:45.001
Consider us your designated drivers.

27:45.003 --> 27:46.436
Us?

27:52.009 --> 27:53.943
You don't look like much
for one of the agency's

27:53.945 --> 27:56.546
highest decorated non-official
cover operatives.

27:56.548 --> 27:58.848
James Bond borrowed my tux.

27:58.850 --> 28:00.350
You know what I think?

28:00.352 --> 28:02.752
I think somewhere under
that 5:00 whiskey stink,

28:02.754 --> 28:04.721
there's a sharp mind still at work.

28:04.723 --> 28:06.089
I think that's why my husband

28:06.091 --> 28:07.757
paid you from a numbered account.

28:07.759 --> 28:10.126
I read about the funeral.

28:10.128 --> 28:11.894
Forgot to send flowers.

28:11.896 --> 28:14.797
Anyone can open the Yellow Pages
and call a private detective.

28:14.799 --> 28:18.067
Only my husband would hire a spy.

28:18.069 --> 28:20.570
(SIGHS) What do you want from me?

28:20.572 --> 28:22.438
Same thing Howard did.

28:22.440 --> 28:24.407
And I'll pay.

28:27.411 --> 28:30.980
What was he looking for?

28:30.982 --> 28:33.049
Not what. (CLEARS THROAT)

28:33.051 --> 28:34.484
Who.

28:34.486 --> 28:36.919
♪

28:36.921 --> 28:38.921
Your son.

28:58.142 --> 29:00.243
(DOOR OPENS)

29:04.081 --> 29:05.448
Surgery?

29:05.450 --> 29:07.183
- Like plastic surgery?
- Yeah.

29:07.185 --> 29:09.319
That explains the Tugenbergs'
bandages the other night.

29:09.321 --> 29:10.386
They're not touching me.

29:10.388 --> 29:12.355
I like my chin. It was my mother's.

29:12.357 --> 29:14.023
Get down.

29:14.025 --> 29:17.293
(BOTH BREATHING HEAVILY)

29:17.295 --> 29:18.528
These people aren't being trained

29:18.530 --> 29:20.596
to impersonate Americans.

29:20.598 --> 29:22.031
They're being trained to replace them.

29:22.033 --> 29:23.766
Yeah.

29:23.768 --> 29:24.767
Let's go.

29:24.769 --> 29:27.270
Their command center is at City Hall.

29:37.214 --> 29:39.549
(MAN GROANING)

29:46.219 --> 29:47.469
_

29:48.392 --> 29:51.294
(ALL MURMURING)

29:51.296 --> 29:52.077
Hmm?

29:52.079 --> 29:54.594
_

30:00.671 --> 30:04.173
This is Cynthia Stegner
at 86 Maplewood Drive.

30:04.175 --> 30:06.843
I'm having an issue with my husband.

30:09.012 --> 30:11.814
(TELEPHONE BEEPS)

30:11.816 --> 30:12.982
They made contact?

30:12.984 --> 30:14.650
I'm into the Crazytown mainframe.

30:14.652 --> 30:15.918
Tom patched us in.

30:15.920 --> 30:17.420
<i>Tell us what we're looking at.</i>

30:17.422 --> 30:19.389
The names of real people
they intend to replace.

30:19.391 --> 30:21.924
<i>An electrician, a mechanic,
a construction worker.</i>

30:21.926 --> 30:23.693
Why replace them? What's the plan?

30:23.695 --> 30:25.661
<i>- We don't know.
- Bob and Linda Tugenberg...</i>

30:25.663 --> 30:27.563
I know them. They're my neighbors.

30:27.565 --> 30:29.699
(ALARM BUZZING, MAN
SPEAKING RUSSIAN OVER P.A.)

30:29.701 --> 30:31.334
- Dumont?
- We lost the link.

30:31.336 --> 30:33.336
Dumont.

30:33.338 --> 30:35.238
Tom, we got a problem.

30:35.240 --> 30:39.041
(MAN CONTINUES SPEAKING
RUSSIAN OVER P.A.)

30:39.043 --> 30:41.411
Someone pulled the plug on their end.
I got nothing.

30:41.413 --> 30:43.379
No, we have identities and addresses.

30:43.381 --> 30:45.248
Go after the construction worker.
Get there fast.

30:45.250 --> 30:46.749
Send a team to follow up on the others.

30:46.751 --> 30:48.251
I'm there. Kick the tires.

30:48.253 --> 30:50.219
- What about Tom and Nez?
- Alert the extraction team

30:50.221 --> 30:51.788
in Russia. They'll be coming fast.

30:51.790 --> 30:53.723
Our focus is the names on that screen.

30:53.725 --> 30:55.958
We need to get to them before
their doppelgangers do.

30:55.960 --> 30:59.095
(DOORBELL RINGS)

30:59.097 --> 31:00.797
What the hell?

31:00.799 --> 31:03.800
♪

31:20.636 --> 31:22.671
(ALARM BLARING)

31:22.673 --> 31:24.973
(MEN SPEAK RUSSIAN)

31:27.661 --> 31:29.829
How much data you think Dumont got?

31:29.831 --> 31:31.598
Not enough.

31:37.771 --> 31:41.641
<i>Well, well, well. I
wonder who you work for.</i>

31:41.643 --> 31:45.478
<i>MI6? CIA? Doesn't matter.</i>

31:45.480 --> 31:48.681
<i>Full of bullets, we all look the same.</i>

31:51.852 --> 31:54.854
♪

32:02.997 --> 32:04.731
MAN: Clear.

32:07.735 --> 32:10.069
Ohh. That's a shame.

32:10.071 --> 32:11.804
Scottie, baby, we got a corpse here

32:11.806 --> 32:13.840
with no sign of the pod people.

32:13.842 --> 32:16.142
Sir? Over here.

32:16.144 --> 32:18.578
He left a note.

32:18.580 --> 32:21.414
"At 6:15 p.m. today, we, the
True Nation Brotherhood

32:21.416 --> 32:22.815
reclaimed our freedom..."
Blah, blah, blah.

32:22.817 --> 32:24.651
"refreshing the tree of liberty..."

32:24.653 --> 32:29.355
Blah, blah. "...rising against
those who would hold us down..."

32:29.357 --> 32:31.391
Hmm. It's 5 of 6:00.

32:31.393 --> 32:32.859
Scottie, we got a suicide note here

32:32.861 --> 32:34.661
taking credit for an attack
that hasn't happened yet.

32:34.663 --> 32:36.829
DUMONT: In addition to the
body Solomon just found,

32:36.831 --> 32:38.398
Robert and Linda Tugenberg...

32:38.400 --> 32:40.933
He runs his own auto-body
shop in Linden, New Jersey.

32:40.935 --> 32:42.435
She's a senior electrical engineer

32:42.437 --> 32:43.970
for the New York Power Authority.

32:43.972 --> 32:46.506
They were both found with
self-inflicted gunshot wounds

32:46.508 --> 32:48.675
by our team 11 minutes ago.

32:48.677 --> 32:50.410
SOLOMON: <i>And let me guess.
Suicide notes?</i>

32:50.412 --> 32:52.278
Taking credit for a crime
that hasn't happened yet.

32:52.280 --> 32:54.247
- But what's the crime?
- Peter Winstone...

32:54.249 --> 32:56.516
He's a construction foreman
with a company credit card.

32:56.518 --> 32:58.418
He used said card an hour ago

32:58.420 --> 33:01.254
to purchase a large amount of Dynex.
Ka-boom.

33:01.256 --> 33:02.789
An electrician, a construction foreman

33:02.791 --> 33:05.224
with heavy explosives, and a mechanic.

33:05.226 --> 33:06.859
They're building a rolling bomb.

33:06.861 --> 33:09.896
I'm finding an online footprint
shared by all three.

33:09.898 --> 33:12.565
Message board postings for
a homegrown militia outfit

33:12.567 --> 33:15.201
- called...
<i>- The True Nation Brotherhood.</i>

33:15.203 --> 33:17.070
This isn't about Russia attacking us.

33:17.072 --> 33:18.538
It's about using their agents

33:18.540 --> 33:20.406
to make us think we've
attacked ourselves.

33:20.408 --> 33:23.543
With suicide notes and dead
Americans to prove it.

33:23.545 --> 33:27.380
The notes... What time do they
say the attack takes place?

33:27.382 --> 33:29.315
6:15. That's 17 minutes from now.

33:29.317 --> 33:31.551
That's how long we have
to find their target.

33:31.553 --> 33:35.154
(ALARM BLARING)

33:35.156 --> 33:36.622
We need a way out of this room.

33:36.624 --> 33:38.257
The extraction point is 6 miles away.

33:38.259 --> 33:39.425
If they're gonna be on our heels,

33:39.427 --> 33:41.094
there's no way we're
gonna make it on foot.

33:41.096 --> 33:44.263
Maybe we don't have to.

33:44.265 --> 33:46.432
(SIGHS) They're gonna blow the door.

33:48.635 --> 33:50.436
How about we blow it for them?

33:50.438 --> 33:52.638
They're wiring those
explosives with blasting caps,

33:52.640 --> 33:54.507
which are stable

33:54.509 --> 33:58.311
but sensitive to stray
electrical current.

33:58.313 --> 34:00.680
I think 10,000 volts ought to do it.

34:02.850 --> 34:06.319
Care to say goodbye?

34:06.321 --> 34:08.187
First off, the stick?

34:08.188 --> 34:10.356
I wasn't moved. You want to honor Gramps

34:10.358 --> 34:11.924
for giving his life for Mother Russia,

34:11.926 --> 34:13.592
we can arrange for you to do the same.

34:13.594 --> 34:16.696
Oh, but before you go, we're Americans,

34:16.697 --> 34:19.264
U.S. of "you have no idea
what's about to happen

34:19.266 --> 34:20.340
to your tired, sadistic..."

34:20.342 --> 34:22.168
All right, I think she probably gets it.

34:24.170 --> 34:25.338
- Ready?
- Mm-hmm.

34:25.340 --> 34:26.839
Here we go.

34:40.821 --> 34:44.824
(ALARMS CONTINUE BLARING)

34:44.826 --> 34:46.893
Damn sirens are gonna
wake up the whole town.

34:46.895 --> 34:48.746
Give me some overwatch while
I hotwire this thing.

34:48.748 --> 34:49.472
Go.

34:53.667 --> 34:55.168
- (GUN COCKS)
- CYNTHIA: What kind of man

34:55.170 --> 34:57.003
runs out on his family?

34:57.005 --> 34:59.572
How'd you find me?

34:59.574 --> 35:02.008
They have ways of tracking us.

35:02.010 --> 35:05.912
♪

35:05.914 --> 35:08.815
Till death do us part, right?

35:08.817 --> 35:10.650
(RING CLINKS)

35:12.617 --> 35:14.133
_

35:14.755 --> 35:16.756
(TIRES SCREECH)

35:16.758 --> 35:18.591
Let's get the hell out of here.

35:20.761 --> 35:22.662
- Do you have a location?
- An area, downtown.

35:22.664 --> 35:24.764
The mechanic rented a
truck this afternoon.

35:24.766 --> 35:26.699
Rental company equips them with GPS.

35:26.701 --> 35:28.067
- We can track the truck.
- Yeah,

35:28.069 --> 35:30.002
moving past Franklin and
Broadway as we speak.

35:30.004 --> 35:32.205
- Get word to Solomon.
- Okay, done and doner.

35:32.207 --> 35:33.639
It's like they want us to find them.

35:33.641 --> 35:35.712
- They <i>do</i> want us to find them.
- Right.

35:35.714 --> 35:37.564
If they're just passing
Franklin and Broadway...

35:37.581 --> 35:38.411
If they're posing as militia,

35:38.413 --> 35:39.998
they'll probably want to
target a government building.

35:40.000 --> 35:42.381
- What's nearby?
- State Supreme Court. Bye!

35:42.383 --> 35:47.119
♪

35:47.121 --> 35:49.755
(TIRES SCREECHING)

35:58.866 --> 36:00.433
I don't suppose it'd be too much to ask

36:00.435 --> 36:01.968
that you turn off the engine

36:01.970 --> 36:03.536
and drop the keys out the window.

36:03.538 --> 36:05.471
We've got 300 pounds of Dynex in here.

36:05.473 --> 36:07.773
Stay back, or it blows.

36:07.775 --> 36:09.242
Yeah, I don't think so.

36:09.244 --> 36:11.110
Fall back, mi amigos.

36:14.414 --> 36:15.648
I'm not really a negotiator.

36:15.650 --> 36:18.050
I don't really know what
people say right now.

36:18.052 --> 36:19.719
You got so much to live for?

36:19.721 --> 36:22.088
Think of your families? I don't know.

36:22.090 --> 36:24.123
I'll say

36:24.125 --> 36:27.560
that was a hell of plot you
guys <i>almost</i> pulled off.

36:27.562 --> 36:32.765
It was elaborate, so... elaborate.

36:32.767 --> 36:34.667
But I bet you that this van
was not supposed to be

36:34.669 --> 36:36.602
the end of your life. Am I right?

36:36.604 --> 36:38.437
So why don't we keep it that way?

36:38.439 --> 36:40.506
Nobody has to leave this
square in a body bag.

36:40.508 --> 36:42.775
Just hand us the detonator,

36:42.777 --> 36:44.644
and we can all go our separate ways.

36:44.646 --> 36:46.779
What do you say, comrade?

36:46.781 --> 36:49.115
I say screw you.

36:49.117 --> 36:52.952
♪

36:52.954 --> 36:54.921
I'm sorry you feel that way.

36:54.923 --> 36:57.657
I didn't want to have to
give the green light.

36:57.659 --> 37:00.259
Green light?

37:00.261 --> 37:01.861
Nice talking to you.

37:01.863 --> 37:03.296
Mi amigos.

37:03.298 --> 37:05.131
(GUNSHOTS)

37:13.564 --> 37:15.632
(TELEPHONES RINGING IN DISTANCE)

37:17.702 --> 37:19.536
Hey, did you hear?

37:19.538 --> 37:23.039
The, uh, satellites show nothing
but a crater where the town was.

37:23.041 --> 37:25.575
The Russians scrubbed the whole thing.

37:25.577 --> 37:27.544
Scottie said she'll ask General Phillips

37:27.546 --> 37:30.547
to provide protection for every
American we got off the drives.

37:30.549 --> 37:32.682
They could still be targeted.
(ELEVATOR BELL CHIMES)

37:35.019 --> 37:37.187
Hey, um...

37:37.189 --> 37:39.656
Thank you.

37:39.658 --> 37:42.926
You saved my life.

37:42.928 --> 37:45.862
5-HTP.

37:45.864 --> 37:48.364
- What?
- The drug they put in the water

37:48.366 --> 37:50.533
destroyed your REM cycle. Take 5-HTP.

37:50.535 --> 37:54.204
It's over-the-counter. It'll
help with the comedown.

37:54.206 --> 37:57.741
How do you know so much about this?

37:57.743 --> 37:59.242
(CHUCKLES)

37:59.244 --> 38:02.245
After you've been a soldier...
Uh, well, no.

38:02.247 --> 38:05.582
After you've seen what people do in war,

38:05.584 --> 38:07.283
they'll offer you every drug there is

38:07.285 --> 38:09.619
except the one you need
to make it go away.

38:09.621 --> 38:11.788
So you try all the others just in case.

38:11.790 --> 38:14.190
(CHUCKLES)

38:14.192 --> 38:17.961
How'd you get sober?

38:17.963 --> 38:20.096
Howard.

38:20.098 --> 38:22.098
This place. (CHUCKLES)

38:22.100 --> 38:24.601
He gave me a job. He...

38:24.603 --> 38:26.770
He helped me clean up.

38:26.772 --> 38:31.441
He gave me a shot at something
I-I never tried before.

38:31.443 --> 38:33.443
Hope.

38:33.445 --> 38:36.112
♪

38:36.114 --> 38:38.748
Do you want... Do you
want to grab a coffee?

38:38.750 --> 38:41.117
Toast to a job well done?

38:41.119 --> 38:44.587
♪

38:44.589 --> 38:45.922
Maybe next time.

38:45.924 --> 38:49.192
♪ If I fall ♪

38:49.194 --> 38:50.660
- Yeah.
- ♪ Can you pull me up?

38:50.662 --> 38:53.997
♪ Can you pull me up? ♪

38:53.999 --> 38:59.836
♪ Where ever you've gone? ♪

38:59.838 --> 39:01.671
DEALER: Damn, girl.

39:01.673 --> 39:05.408
I was hoping you'd be one of
the ones who stayed gone.

39:05.410 --> 39:10.780
♪ I just need to know ♪

39:10.782 --> 39:16.686
♪ That you won't forget about me ♪

39:16.688 --> 39:22.292
♪ Where ever you've gone? ♪

39:22.294 --> 39:27.530
♪ How, how, how? ♪

39:27.532 --> 39:30.099
- Reading a bedtime story?
- ♪ I just need to know ♪

39:30.101 --> 39:32.202
Read it a thousand times...

39:32.204 --> 39:37.307
Wealthy couple, beautiful
son, trip to Ocean City.

39:37.309 --> 39:39.275
Before he died, Howard hired someone

39:39.277 --> 39:42.111
to track down our son, Christopher.

39:42.113 --> 39:45.181
Track him?

39:45.183 --> 39:48.051
I don't understand. I
thought your son was dead.

39:48.053 --> 39:50.720
I talked to the man.

39:50.722 --> 39:55.225
He found a record of a child
services in Wilmington,

39:55.227 --> 39:59.729
less than 20 miles from where
Christopher disappeared.

39:59.731 --> 40:03.233
A boy Chris' age.

40:03.235 --> 40:05.168
Blue eyes, brown hair.

40:05.170 --> 40:06.936
His name was Christopher.

40:06.938 --> 40:08.605
A week after we lost our boy,

40:08.607 --> 40:10.306
that boy was brought to child services.

40:10.308 --> 40:12.842
But you told me your husband
was out of his mind,

40:12.844 --> 40:15.912
that his search for
Christopher was a delusion.

40:15.914 --> 40:18.982
- I thought he was.
- ♪ How, how, how? ♪

40:18.984 --> 40:21.751
- Now I don't know.
- ♪ I just need to know ♪

40:21.753 --> 40:23.253
But as the head of one of the largest

40:23.255 --> 40:25.588
intelligence operations in the world,

40:25.590 --> 40:28.091
if there is any chance he's out there,

40:28.093 --> 40:29.993
I will find my son.

40:29.995 --> 40:32.428
♪ That you won't forget about me ♪

40:32.430 --> 40:35.098
I'm telling you, she is coming for me.

40:35.100 --> 40:37.000
(SIGHS)

40:37.002 --> 40:39.936
Operation North Star... I need
to know exactly what you found.

40:39.938 --> 40:41.404
She knows about the investigator.

40:41.406 --> 40:43.606
She knows that, uh, you
hired him to find me.

40:43.608 --> 40:44.941
- She...
- Tom.

40:44.943 --> 40:48.211
What did you learn?

40:48.213 --> 40:49.846
It's a sleeper program.

40:49.848 --> 40:52.115
It's one that trains agents, cuts them

40:52.117 --> 40:56.219
to look exactly like the people
they're assigned to replace.

40:56.221 --> 40:57.787
Oh.

41:00.024 --> 41:02.625
- So it's true.
- What's true?

41:02.627 --> 41:04.360
You know about this place?

41:04.362 --> 41:08.264
Two months after your disappearance,

41:08.266 --> 41:11.100
your mother was in a
terrible car accident.

41:11.102 --> 41:12.902
Some thought she was
trying to end her life,

41:12.904 --> 41:15.438
that the pain of losing
you was too much.

41:15.440 --> 41:17.307
She was in the hospital for four months.

41:17.309 --> 41:19.909
After that, she was never the same.

41:19.911 --> 41:23.279
I noticed the differences,
but I assumed it was because

41:23.281 --> 41:25.815
no one is ever the same
after the loss of a child.

41:25.817 --> 41:28.584
It was only years later
that I began to suspect

41:28.586 --> 41:30.653
that there was something more to it.

41:30.655 --> 41:34.057
And when your mother
learned of my suspicions,

41:34.059 --> 41:36.092
- she tried to have me killed.
- You told me this part.

41:36.094 --> 41:37.961
You came to suspect who
she was working with,

41:37.963 --> 41:39.662
- where her loyalties lie.
- I'm not talking about

41:39.664 --> 41:42.799
who she's working with.
I'm talking about her.

41:42.801 --> 41:46.169
I wasn't gonna tell you this
until after it was confirmed.

41:46.171 --> 41:49.172
But I believe that Scottie Hargrave

41:49.174 --> 41:51.240
is a sleeper agent.

41:51.242 --> 41:53.509
Wha...

41:53.511 --> 41:56.112
N-No.

41:56.114 --> 41:58.147
- No, that can't be true.
- It is.

41:58.149 --> 41:59.949
That program, the doubles,

41:59.951 --> 42:02.285
the town, the people who ran it...

42:02.287 --> 42:04.821
I believe that 30 years ago,

42:04.823 --> 42:07.190
they murdered your mother.

